CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 18, 1961, page 15, reads: "Sequoires Tri-Hi-Y Club Members - Participating annually in the teen talk discussion course is the Sequoires Tri-Hi-Club of the Centre Avenue YMCA. The course invited high school age men and women to weight various teen-age problems. The Sequoires are shown above with their Schenley High Hi-Y Club guests. Left to right: Patricia Redmond, president of the Sequoires: Joyce Ray, Andrea Williams, Edith Dinkins, Inoa Geter, Timothy Stevens, Bennie Scott, Carol Alston, Bernard Thomas, David Ruffin, Dewayne Talley, Carol Higgins, moderator; Audrey Walton, Yvonne Walton, Patsy Austin, Yvonne Banks, Delphine Freeman, Joyce Lesesne, Nadine Woodward, Robert Coy, William McCaskill, Jeannette Finch, William Cook, adviser for the Schenley Hi-Y Club, and Mrs. Thelma Lovette, adviser for the Sequoires. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of eight men and sixteen women, members of the Sequoires and Tri-Hi-Y Club, left to right: Patricia Redmond, Joyce Ray, Andrea Williams, Edith Dinkins, Inoa Geter, Timothy "Tim" Stevens, Bennie Scott, Carol Alston, Bernard Thomas, David Ruffin, Dewayne Talley, Carol Higgins, Audrey Walton, Yvonne Walton, Patsy Austin, Yvonne Banks, Delphine Freeman, Joyce Lesesne, Nadine Woodward, Robert Coy, William McCaskill, Jeannette Finch, William Cook, and Thelma Lovette, gathered around table in interior with checkerboard linoleum floor
